# JAQL Testing

Full reference: [docs/testing-strategy.md](docs/testing-strategy.md)

## File Mapping

`include/jaql/<module>/<header>.hpp` → `tests/unit/<module>/test_<header>.cpp`

## Naming

`TEST(ClassName, MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedOutcome)` — three underscore-separated parts.

## Rules

1. One test per logical behaviour, not one test per function.
2. Every `Result<T>` function needs explicit error-path tests.
3. Never compare `double` with `==` — use `EXPECT_NEAR` or `JAQL_EXPECT_NEAR_REL`.
4. Use `ASSERT_TRUE(result.has_value()) << result.error().message();` before dereferencing `Result<T>`.
5. No `using namespace` at file scope.
6. Use `static_assert` for compile-time invariants where applicable.
7. Update `tests/unit/<module>/CMakeLists.txt` when adding test files.

## Validation

After adding tests, run `./scripts/test.sh` or build the specific test target.
